  "response_text": "Here's a healthy breakfast plan for a week, with a different meal idea for each day:\n\n**Monday: Greek Yogurt Parfait**\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)\n- 1/4 cup granola\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1/2 cup sliced banana\n\n**Tuesday: Avocado Toast**\n- 1 slice whole-grain bread, toasted\n- 1/2 avocado, mashed\n- 1 egg, poached or scrambled\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Optional: cherry tomatoes or spinach for added flavor\n\n**Wednesday: Overnight Oats**\n- 1/2 cup rolled oats\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/4 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1/2 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)\n- 1 tablespoon chia seeds\n\nCombine oats, almond milk, Greek yogurt, and honey in a jar or container. Refrigerate overnight and top with berries and chia seeds in the morning.\n\n**Thursday: Smoothie Bowl**\n- 1 cup frozen mixed berries\n- 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk\n- 1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1/2 cup sliced almonds\n- 1/2 cup shredded coconut\n- 1/2 cup sliced fresh fruit (such as banana or mango)\n\nCombine berries, almond milk, and Greek yogurt in a blender. Top with sliced almonds, shredded coconut, and fresh fruit.\n\n**Friday: Whole-Grain Waffles with Fresh Fruit and Nuts**\n- 1 whole-grain waffle\n- 1/2 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)\n- 1/4 cup chopped walnuts\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n\n**Saturday: Breakfast Burrito**\n- 1 whole-grain tortilla\n- 2 scrambled eggs\n- 1/4 cup black beans, cooked\n- 1/4 cup shredded cheese (low-fat)\n- 1/4 cup diced bell peppers\n- Salsa or hot sauce (optional)\n\n**Sunday: Cinnamon Oatmeal with Banana and Nuts**\n- 1/2 cup cooked oatmeal\n- 1/2 cup sliced banana\n- 1 tablespoon chopped walnuts\n- 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n\nRemember to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day. You can also customize these meal ideas to suit your dietary preferences and ingredient availability.",
